            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1580808083881-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained kidney beans</strong> to the pan along with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and your <strong>tomato paste</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened to a bolognese-like consistency, then remove from the heat – this is your <strong>meat-free mince chilli</strong></p><p>Tip: Add an extra splash of water if it's looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
